4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING THE QUALITY EDUCATOR LOAN
5 ASSISTANCE PROGRAM; EXPANDING ELIGIBILITY FOR THE PROGRAM TO INCLUDE ALL NEWLY
6 HIRED QUALITY EDUCATORS IN MONTANA PUBLIC SCHOOLS; PROVIDING THAT NEWLY HIRED
7 QUALITY EDUCATORS IN IMPACTED SCHOOLS HAVE PRIORITY FOR RECEIVING LOAN ASSISTANCE
8 PAYMENTS; PROVIDING A PROCESS TO PRORATE LOAN ASSISTANCE PAYMENTS IF THE
9 APPROPRIATION IS INSUFFICIENT TO FULLY FUND THE LOAN ASSISTANCE PAYMENT FOR ALL
10 ELIGIBLE QUALITY EDUCATORS; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-4-503, 20-4-504, AND 20-4-505, MCA; AND
11 PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 Section 1. Section 20-4-503, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "20-4-503. Critical quality educator shortages -- impacted schools. (1) The board of public
17 education, in consultation with the office of public instruction, shall maintain and make publicly available a
18 current list of impacted schools.
19 (2) A quality educator working at an impacted school is eligible for repayment of all or part of the
20 quality educator's outstanding educational loans existing at the time of application in accordance with the
21 eligibility and award criteria established under this part. If a quality educator is eligible for loan assistance and
22 remains employed in the same impacted school or another impacted school within the same school district, the
23 quality educator remains eligible for a lifetime total of up to 3 years of state-funded loan repayment assistance
24 and an additional 1 year of loan repayment assistance funded by the impacted school or the district under
25 which the impacted school is operated pursuant to 20-4-504(2)."
26
27 Section 2. Section 20-4-504, MCA, is amended to read:
28 "20-4-504. Loan repayment assistance. (1) Loan repayment assistance may be provided on behalf
