5 Section 3. Section 20-4-505, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "20-4-505. Loan repayment assistance documentation. (1) A quality educator shall submit an
7 application for loan repayment assistance to the superintendent of public instruction in accordance with policies
8 and procedures adopted by the superintendent of public instruction. The application must include official
9 verification or proof of the applicant's total unpaid accumulated educational loan debt and other documentation
10 required by the superintendent of public instruction that is necessary for verification of the applicant's eligibility.
11 (2) The superintendent of public instruction may require a quality educator who is eligible for loan
12 repayment assistance to provide documentation that the quality educator has exhausted repayment assistance
13 from other federal, state, or local loan forgiveness, discharge, or repayment incentive programs.
14 (3) The superintendent of public instruction may remit payment of the loan on behalf of the quality
15 educator in accordance with the requirements of this part and policies and procedures adopted by the
16 superintendent of public instruction.
17 (4) An impacted A school or a school district under which an impacted school is operated may
18 remit payment of the loan on behalf of a quality educator eligible for loan repayment assistance under this
19 section in accordance with 20-4-504."
